Think there's a use case for this - especially if we have desk shares and highly NDA'd clients that may require longer term conference room space (e.g. Adidas in our past). 

In general, my sense is that the mix of desk shares makes this a useful line item.

attachments.fallback: [September 14th, 2015 10:19 AM] john: Hey arya-ers. I printed up some blank floorplans in case you'd be willing to sketch in some of your ideas of how the office layout could be. Don't worry, it is not some kind of "we'll pick one  of those" sorts of things, but more a way to start creating ideas about layout/flow. The printouts are by the foamcore "Project Arya" sign in the middle wall bay in 390 area. The scale is off (I inflated them to use more of the paper) but lengthwise the distance between columns is 26'. and there's a weird stair spur at the top left which is because they accidentally used floor 2 to give us a blank floor. We don't have that spur! Oh and bathroom layouts are supposed to flipped to keep the doors further away from the elevator.
